external_knowledge:
Top commenters refers to users with the highest total comments across distinct articles; 
Users are ranked based on the total comments made in descending order (i.e., the user with the most comments is ranked 1); 
The query only considers the top 3 users with the highest ranks.

sql:
SELECT tag_name
FROM tags
WHERE tag_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- "Sought-after" refers to articles that have received the most interactions; 
- Interactions are calculated by adding likes, views, and comments; 
- Only published articles are considered.

sql:
SELECT title
FROM articles
ORDER BY publish_date DESC, view_count DESC;
